SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-50-1001(b)(2), is amended by
deleting the subdivision and substituting the following:
(2) Subject to Section 3, determine the salary and terms of employment for
employees of state special schools;
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-50-1001(c), is amended by
deleting the language "For the purposes of this part" and substituting "As used in this part" and
by adding the following as a new, appropriately designated subdivision:
( ) "Teacher":
(A) Unless the context requires otherwise, means a person licensed by
the state board of education and employed at a state special school; and
(B) Does not include:
(i) The chief administrative officer of a state special school; and
(ii) Those who are considered state employees for leave
purposes under title 8, chapter 50, part 8.
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-50-1001, is amended by adding
the following as a new, appropriately designated subsection:
( ) In managing and controlling the state special schools, the department of
education must provide the following to the teachers of state special schools:
(1) Eligibility to accumulate and use leave in the same manner as public
school teachers under chapter 5, part 7 of this title; and
